HEADWORD: Timbale
<hw>Tim`bale"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., prop., a
kettledrum; -- so named from the form of the mold used. Cf.
<er>Timbal</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Cookery)</fld> <def>A seasoned
preparation, as of chicken, lobster, cheese, or fish, cooked in a
drum-shaped mold; also, a pastry case, usually small, filled with a
cooked mixture.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

